{"id":2360,"date":"2013-03-04T07:10:17","date_gmt":"2013-03-04T13:10:17","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/buycom.php"},"modified":"2013-03-04T07:10:17","modified_gmt":"2013-03-04T13:10:17","slug":"buycom","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/buycom.php","title":{"rendered":"Buy.com"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/buy_dot_com_logo.gif\" alt=\"Buy.com Logo, Before and After\" \/><\/p>\n<p><strong>About: <\/strong> (Buy.com Est. 1997 \/ Rakuten Est. 1997) &#8220;<a href=\"http:\/\/www.rakuten.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Buy.com<\/a> joined the Rakuten family in 2010, making the joint businesses combined into one of the world&#8217;s largest online retail marketplaces. We offer consumers more than 90 million products from 38,500 merchants around the globe. Buy.com becoming Rakuten.com Shopping is the next step of that relationship as the Rakuten Group increasingly unifies its brand internationally. This transition will open up the Rakuten.com Shopping (formerly Buy.com) marketplace to customers globally, as well as introducing merchants and retailers from around the world to its North American customer base. Both its merchants and its consumers will benefit from this open, global market. We are excited at the possibilities to come, and we hope you continue to join us in our global growth.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p><strong>Design by:<\/strong> N\/A.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Ed.&#8217;s Notes:<\/strong> This isn&#8217;t so much a logo before\/after but a brand before\/after and the effects of corporate ownership. Buy.com didn&#8217;t have much of a logo before and Rakuten doesn&#8217;t have much of a logo either, just an &#8220;R&#8221; inside a circle that has been passed off to Buy.com. The real problem here is going from the &uuml;ber simple &#8220;Buy.com&#8221; to the utterly unmemorable and confusing &#8220;Rakuten.com Shopping&#8221;. If that weren&#8217;t enough, there is a video, below (or after the jump) that makes all the employees shown look as humiliated as the old Buy.com logo probably feels.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Relevant links:<\/strong> <a href=\"http:\/\/www.rakuten.com\/ct\/aboutus.aspx?omadtrack=campaignrebrand10x_homepage_feature1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Buy.com is now Rakuten.com Shopping<\/a>.<\/p><!--more-->            <object width=\"574\" height=\"323\" type=\"application\/x-shockwave-flash\" data=\"http:\/\/images.rakuten.com\/buy_assets\/flashplayers\/BuyPlayer.swf\"><!-- Firefox uses the `data` attribute above, IE\/Safari uses the param below -->\n               <param name=\"movie\" value=\"http:\/\/images.rakuten.com\/buy_assets\/flashplayers\/BuyPlayer.swf\" \/>\n               <param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\" \/>\n               <param name=\"wmode\" value=\"transparent\" \/>\n               <param name=\"flashvars\" value=\"&amp;loaderURL=http:\/\/images.rakuten.com\/buy_assets\/videoreviews\/screens\/2013\/01\/firstframe_wer.png&amp;videoURL=http:\/\/videos.buy.com\/videos\/addeals\/rakuten\/wer_i.mp4\"\/>\n               <!-- fallback to HTML5 playback: -->\n               <video width=\"574\" height=\"323\" controls=\"controls\" poster=\"http:\/images.rakuten.com\/buy_assets\/addeals\/rakuten\/rakuten_video_thumb.png\" width=\"533\" height=\"323\">\n               <!-- MP4 must be first for iPad --><source src=\"http:\/\/videos.buy.com\/videos\/addeals\/rakuten\/wer_i.mp4\" type=\"video\/mp4\"\/><!-- Safari \/ iOS video    -->\n               <!-- placeholder image if no video playback available-->\n               <img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/images.rakuten.com\/buy_assets\/addeals\/rakuten\/video_bg.jpg\" width=\"533\" height=\"323\" alt=\"Rakuten.com Shopping\"\/>\n               <\/video>\n            <\/object>\n<p class=\"bottom\">Thanks to Flint Johnston for the tip.<\/p>",